# [PLANTS](../wg/plants.html)

## Summary

The PLANTS Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss the status of its core draft, explore log reconciliation alternatives, evaluate deployment use cases for private PKIs, review real-world post-quantum cryptography (PQC) measurements, and receive updates from the recent Hackathon. 

Key outcomes of the meeting included a design decision on how to represent trust anchor IDs in Merkle Tree Certificates (MTCs), a proposal for Git-rebase-style log reconciliation to handle log forks, and a discussion on how to modularize deployment use cases for private and community PKIs.

